President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring April 16, 2019, as "Education and Sharing Day, U.S.A." In the proclamation, he highlights the importance of education in a strong republic and the role it plays in shaping the character of citizens and their representatives. The proclamation recognizes Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson, the Lubavitcher Rebbe, for his commitment to education and his contributions to humanity. President Trump emphasizes the need for educational freedom and the importance of open debate and free inquiry in higher learning institutions. He calls upon government officials, educators, volunteers, and all Americans to observe this day with appropriate programs and activities that promote lifelong learning, freedom of expression, and virtue.